FBIS4-61699 "drsov089_f_94016" FBIS-SOV-94-089 Daily Report 9 May 1994 National Affairs Council Set Up To Protect Ukrainian Statehood Council Set Up To Protect Ukrainian Statehood WS0905144894 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in Ukrainian 1400 GMT 9 May 94 WS0905144894 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network Ukrainian BFN [Text] Creation of the Ukrainian Civil Council of the Crimea, UHRK, has been announced today in Simferopol at an expanded meeting of the Congress of Crimean Ukrainians with the participation of representatives of democratic parties, public organizations, and movements that operate on the peninsula. The Ukrainian Civil Council of the Crimea is a nationally-oriented parliament-type of representative body of the national and democratic forces. It was noted at the meeting that the establishment of this body was prompted by the Crimean crisis which is continuing to grow and is assuming a dangerous form. [word indistinct] of the Ukrainian Civil Council of the Crimea has set its primary goal as ensuring the inviolability of the Ukrainian borders, protecting and strengthening Ukrainian statehood in the Crimea, and maintaining political stability, peace and ethnic accord on the peninsula. The Ukrainian Civil Council [word indistinct] to craft alternative draft laws. It will help deputies of the democratic forces enter the parliament, promote forging of the pro-Ukrainian opposition in the Crimean Supreme Soviet, and provide [words indistinct] support.
